nodes.bodyText:
This is a very rare case I ran into where postCompilationTasks() could be triggered twice. A steam failure exception might be thrown inside postCompilationTasks(), although the compilation is already successful at the server . This exception is caught in CompilationInfoPerThreadBase::compile() and setCompilation(NULL)  is called before postCompilationTasks() is called.
However it only happens when sending free KOT messages. Since I'm going to remove this message, I plan to revert this change because we don't have other known cases that hits this path.
CompilationInfoPerThreadBase::compile()
try 
{ 
	…
	postCompilationTasks();
}
catch 
{
	…
	postCompilationTasks();
}
https://github.com/eclipse/openj9/blob/ed3d30eedefeef319a1908a98556262ec8fa7c1e/runtime/compiler/control/CompilationThread.cpp#L7752-L7762.

